[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man in critical condition after being hit by vehicle in Paisley

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An 18-year-old man is in a critical condition in hospital after he was hit by a vehicle in Paisley.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened on Wellmeadow Street, near to Lady Lane, at about 05:00.
Emergency services attended and the man was taken to the Royal Alexandra Hospital before being transferred to the Queen Elizabeth University Hospital.
Police Scotland has appealed for witnesses to come forward.
